atriz Pascual]]|ESP}}||''' 1:36:03''' ||\n|-\n| 21 ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Sonata Milu\u0161auskait\u0117]]|LTU}}||'''1:36:20''' ||\n|-\n| 22 ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Monica Svensson]]|SWE}}||'''1:38:25''' ||\n|-\n!colspan=\"4\"|DID NOT FINISH (DNF)\n|-\n| &mdash; ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Kristina Saltanovi\u010d]]|LTU}}||'''DNF'''\n|-\n!colspan=\"4\"|DISQUALIFIED (DSQ)\n|-\n| &mdash; ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Elena Ginko]]|BLR}}||'''DSQ'''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2006 Race Walking Year Ranking]]\n\n==References==\n* [http://www.tilastopaja.org/staticresults/eaa9235808.htm Official results]\n* [http://todor66.com/athletics/europe/2006/Women_20km_Walk.html Results]\n<br />\n{{EC20kmwalk}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2006 European Athletics Championships - Women's 20 kilometres walk}}\n[[Category:Events at the 2006 European Athletics Championships|Walk 20 km]]\n[[Category:Racewalking at the European Athletics Championships]]\n[[Category:2006 in women's athletics]]\n\n\n{{Athletics-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{2006AthleticsEC}}\nThe '''[[Race walking|Women's 20&nbsp;km walk]]''' event at the '''[[2006 European Championships in Athletics|2006 European Championships]]''' was held on August 9, 2006 in [[Gothenburg, Sweden]], with the start at 17:15h.\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''Gold'''||{{flagicon|BLR}} [[Ryta Turava]]<br />''[[Belarus]] <small>(BLR)</small>''\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"silver\"|'''Silver'''||{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Olga Kaniskina]]<br />''[[Russia]] <small>(RUS)</small>''\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"CC9966\"|'''Bronze'''||{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Elisa Rigaudo]]<br />''[[Italy]] <small>(ITA)</small>''\n|}\n\n==Abbreviations==\n*''All times shown are in hours:minutes:seconds''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|'''DNS''' || did not start\n|-\n|'''NM''' || no mark\n|-\n|'''WR''' || world record\n|-\n|'''WL''' || world leading\n|-\n